 1593     }
 1594   
 1595     /* Level2 S-Function Block: '<S2>/CellV11' (LCInport) */
 1596     {
 1597       SimStruct *rts = Batterymodel_HiL_M->childSfunctions[78];
 1598       sfcnUpdate(rts, 1);
 1599       if (ssGetErrorStatus(rts) != (NULL))
 1600         return;
 1601     }
 1602   
 1603     /* Level2 S-Function Block: '<S2>/CellV12' (LCInport) */
 1604     {
 1605       SimStruct *rts = Batterymodel_HiL_M->childSfunctions[79];
 1606       sfcnUpdate(rts, 1);
 1607       if (ssGetErrorStatus(rts) != (NULL))
 1608         return;
 1609     }
 1610   
 1611     /* Level2 S-Function Block: '<S3>/Error_CellNo' (LCInport) */
 1612     {
 1613       SimStruct *rts = Batterymodel_HiL_M->childSfunctions[80];
 1614       sfcnUpdate(rts, 1);
 1615       if (ssGetErrorStatus(rts) != (NULL))
 1616         return;
 1617     }
 1618   
 1619     /* Level2 S-Function Block: '<S3>/Error_Event' (LCInport) */
 1620     {
 1621       SimStruct *rts = Batterymodel_HiL_M->childSfunctions[81];
 1622       sfcnUpdate(rts, 1);
 1623       if (ssGetErrorStatus(rts) != (NULL))
 1624         return;
 1625     }
 1626   
 1627     /* Level2 S-Function Block: '<S3>/Error_Indication' (LCInport) */
 1628     {
 1629       SimStruct *rts = Batterymodel_HiL_M->childSfunctions[82];
 1630       sfcnUpdate(rts, 1);
 1631       if (ssGetErrorStatus(rts) != (NULL))
 1632         return;
 1633     }
 1634   
 1635     /* Update absolute time for base rate */
 1636     /* The "clockTick0" counts the number of times the code of this task has
 1637      * been executed. The absolute time is the multiplication of "clockTick0"
 1638      * and "Timing.stepSize0". Size of "clockTick0" ensures timer will not
 1639      * overflow during the application lifespan selected.
 1640      * Timer of this task consists of two 32 bit unsigned integers.
 1641      * The two integers represent the low bits Timing.clockTick0 and the high bits
 1642      * Timing.clockTickH0. When the low bit overflows to 0, the high bits increment.
 1643      */
 1644     if (!(++Batterymodel_HiL_M->Timing.clockTick0)) {
 1645       ++Batterymodel_HiL_M->Timing.clockTickH0;
 1646     }
 1647   
 1648     Batterymodel_HiL_M->Timing.t[0] = Batterymodel_HiL_M->Timing.clockTick0 *
 1649       Batterymodel_HiL_M->Timing.stepSize0 +
 1650       Batterymodel_HiL_M->Timing.clockTickH0 *
 1651       Batterymodel_HiL_M->Timing.stepSize0 * 4294967296.0;
 1652   
 1653     {
 1654       /* Update absolute timer for sample time: [0.01s, 0.0s] */
 1655       /* The "clockTick1" counts the number of times the code of this task has
 1656        * been executed. The absolute time is the multiplication of "clockTick1"
 1657        * and "Timing.stepSize1". Size of "clockTick1" ensures timer will not
 1658        * overflow during the application lifespan selected.
 1659        * Timer of this task consists of two 32 bit unsigned integers.
 1660        * The two integers represent the low bits Timing.clockTick1 and the high bits
 1661        * Timing.clockTickH1. When the low bit overflows to 0, the high bits increment.
 1662        */
 1663       if (!(++Batterymodel_HiL_M->Timing.clockTick1)) {
 1664         ++Batterymodel_HiL_M->Timing.clockTickH1;
 1665       }
 1666   
 1667       Batterymodel_HiL_M->Timing.t[1] = Batterymodel_HiL_M->Timing.clockTick1 *
 1668         Batterymodel_HiL_M->Timing.stepSize1 +
 1669         Batterymodel_HiL_M->Timing.clockTickH1 *
 1670         Batterymodel_HiL_M->Timing.stepSize1 * 4294967296.0;
 1671     }
 1672   
 1673     /* tid is required for a uniform function interface.
 1674      * Argument tid is not used in the function. */
 1675     UNUSED_PARAMETER(tid);
 1676   }
